================================================================================
                           PROJECT DESCRIPTION
================================================================================

ESP32-DIV HaleHound Edition is a substantial rewrite of the original ESP32-DIV
firmware, designed for ESP32-based wireless security research and penetration
testing devices. This edition focuses on stability, expanded functionality,
and continued support for V1 hardware.

HALEHOUND EDITION ENHANCEMENTS:

  Core Improvements:
    - 30+ bug fixes including v2.5.0 stability improvements
    - SPI bus architecture overhaul for reliable peripheral communication
    - Centralized touch calibration system for DIY builds
    - Memory management optimizations
    - TX/RX pin swap fix for CC1101 SubGHz module

  New Features:
    - Spectrum Analyzer with visual frequency display
    - ProtoKill - Protocol disruption capabilities
    - WLAN Jammer functionality
    - WiFi Deauther complete overhaul
    - Scanner/Spectrum Analyzer complete redesign
    - Skull wave activity spinner animation
    - Enhanced menu system and UI improvements

  Accessibility:
    - Duggie Edition support for accessibility needs
    - Configurable display and input options
    - Touch calibration persistence

  Hardware Support:
    - Continued V1 board support (ESP32-WROOM-32U)
    - V2 board compatibility (ESP32-S3)
    - CC1101 SubGHz module integration
    - NRF24L01 support
    - TFT display with XPT2046 touch


